This is a simple web based editor for Force.com Apex and Visualforce. It aspires to be the textpad/notepad of Force.com development tools.

What currently works (not a lot)

* You can login to a Salesforce Org
* It will retrieve your Apex code and Visualforce pages
* basic apex syntax highlighting
* You can edit stuff but not save it (see I said not a lot)

Setup

The instructions here will get you started: http://dailyjs.com/2010/11/08/node-tutorial-2/

* Node.js - http://nodejs.org/
* mongodb - http://www.mongodb.org/
* npm - https://github.com/isaacs/npm
* A bunch of modules.
    Install via npm:
        cd Ockley
        npm install express connect-mongodb mongoose mustache mustachio sax
* run mongod
* run Ockley (node app.js)


    
